> A slice = **one module or one screen**. It is done when every applicable box below is checked.
> The `../standards-kb/` domain links each carry their own **Acceptance checklist** —
> satisfy it, then tick. The final gate is the **99 Master Release Gate**.

**Slice:** [MODULE_OR_SCREEN] · **PR:** [#NNN] · **Author:** [AI/owner] · **Date:** [YYYY-MM-DD]

## Core (every slice)
- [ ] Scope matches one module/screen; spec + plan linked.
- [ ] Follows `../CLAUDE.md` (stack, conventions, multi-tenancy rules).
- [ ] Reversible defaults logged in `DECISIONS.md` → Assumptions; new forks recorded as ADRs.
- [ ] UI (if any) uses `../design-system-kb/` tokens — no hardcoded colors/spacing/type.

